Privacy Policy for JIRA Assistant Worklog Indicator

Last updated: [Current Date]

1. Data Collection and Usage
This extension collects and stores the following data locally in your browser:
- User preferences (work hour settings)
- Color threshold values
- Language preferences
- User names (visible from JIRA Assistant interface, but not stored separately)

2. Data Storage
All data is stored locally in your browser using Chrome's storage API. No data is transmitted to external servers or third parties.

3. Data Access
- The extension only accesses data on the JIRA Assistant web interface (https://app.jiraassistant.com)
- User names are only read from the webpage to apply color indicators
- All settings are stored locally and can be exported or deleted by the user at any time

4. Data Sharing
We do not:
- Collect or store personal data on external servers
- Share any data with third parties
- Use data for any purpose other than the extension's core functionality

5. User Control
Users can:
- Export their settings to a local JSON file
- Import settings from a previously exported file
- Clear all stored data by removing the extension
- Modify their settings at any time through the extension interface

6. Updates to Privacy Policy
Users will be notified of any changes to this privacy policy through the extension's update notes in the Chrome Web Store.

7. Contact
For privacy concerns or questions, please contact us through the Chrome Web Store support channel.

8. Consent
By installing and using this extension, you consent to the data handling practices described in this privacy policy.
